genresAdvancedInfo.name: irish underground rap
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A subgenre of hip-hop that focuses on the gritty realities of life in Ireland's urban areas. Irish underground rap often features socially conscious lyrics that touch on issues such as poverty, crime, and inequality. With a raw and unfiltered sound, this genre provides a platform for Irish artists to express their perspectives and experiences.
